history.content:
Want to build a powerful network of technologists, meet inspiring tech industry leaders, and learn from professional workshops?

As a Harvard WECode Lead Technology Fellow, I'm excited to invite you to attend Harvard WECode’s first virtual undergraduate conference on March 6-7, 2021 in our effort to cultivate the next generation of technical leaders, foster a community amongst students passionate about tech, and promote inclusivity for young women and non-binary technologists excited to make a change in the world.

 

Conference events include…

✔ Keynote speakers (more to come!):
- Chief Technology Officer at Polaris, Anjana Rajan
- Founder & CEO of College Code, Chelsea C. Williams
✔ Career Fair & workshops led by reps from Facebook, Google, Bloomberg LP, and more
✔ Panels on health tech, environmental tech, and social impact

Check out harvardwecode.com for more details.

Please email me at sophie2220@berkeley.edu by Saturday, January 9th at 11:59 pm EST if you would like to receive a referral link for a 30% discount on your early registration ticket. Hope to see you there!
